3483B55A2E0353E4E15500000A600446.description: The Line of Business of the intermediary system as defined in the System application.
3483B55A2E0353E4E15500000A600446.name: LineOfBusinessIntermediary

53CDE5310DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: A name that can be used to access a service, used for RFC destination, for example.
53CDE5310DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: ServiceAccessName

53CDE5350DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The name of a function module, a procedure, an HTTP method, a web service operation, or similar type of relatively low level executable.
53CDE5350DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: ServiceFunctionName

53CDE5B70DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The value of a string parameter.
53CDE5B70DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: ParameterValueString

53CDE5BB0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The direction of the parameter: input, output, or input and output.
53CDE5BB0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: ParameterDirection

53CDE5E50DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The level of risk associated with an action or resource, etc.
53CDE5E50DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: GenericRiskLevel

53CDE5EB0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The action name or action code, usually the verb of the event, such as create.
53CDE5EB0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: GenericAction

53CDE6090DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The time at which the event was observed or reported.
53CDE6090DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: Timestamp

53CDE60B0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The type of the actor system, for example, ABAP.
53CDE60B0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: SystemTypeActor

53CDE60D0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The ID of the actor system of the event, for example, SID/client ID for an ABAP system.
53CDE60D0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: SystemIdActor

53CDE6110DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The name of a middle level of a hierarchy of execution. The hierarchy goes from workflow, to transaction, to program, to function.
53CDE6110DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: ServiceTransactionName

53CDE6130DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The name of a program or report.
53CDE6130DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: ServiceProgramName

53CDE6150DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The type of log that the event comes from. This is set in the log learning process.
53CDE6150DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: EventLogType

53CDE6170DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The local part of the hostname of the initiator of the event.
53CDE6170DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkHostnameInitiator

53CDE61B0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: The name of the service instance. For SAP Netweaver Application Server ABAP, the instance name identifies server, system and instance number.
53CDE61B0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: ServiceInstanceName

53CDE61D0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.description: Event name or event code. Either a code that identifies the log entry type, or a text that describes the event.
53CDE61D0DC572EEE10000000A4CF109.name: EventCode

53D7869BD32C1B2EE10000000A4CF109.description: Role of the actor system, for example, test, production, customizing.
53D7869BD32C1B2EE10000000A4CF109.name: SystemRoleActor

53D8FCF497FB1B2EE10000000A4CF109.description: The pseudonym of the acting user involved in the event.  In many events an acting user and/or actor system performs an action on a targeted user. A targeted user may be the target of actions such as create, alter, delete, log on, log off, etc.
53D8FCF497FB1B2EE10000000A4CF109.name: UserPseudonymActing

53D8FCF897FB1B2EE10000000A4CF109.description: For an ABAP system, this is the user group in user master maintenance. The acting user belongs to this group.
53D8FCF897FB1B2EE10000000A4CF109.name: UserGroupActing

53DABB1D5D7C293FE10000000A4CF109.description: Used to correlate log instances at the top level, for example, the root context ID of an SAP passport.
53DABB1D5D7C293FE10000000A4CF109.name: CorrelationId

53EE564D1AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.description: The alert number is consecutive and unique.
53EE564D1AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.name: alertNumber

53EE564E1AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.description: Display name of the pattern that raised the alert.
53EE564E1AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.name: patternDisplayName

53EE56521AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.description: Timestamp when the alert was created in local server time.
53EE56521AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.name: alertCreationTimestamp

53EE56531AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.description: The pseudonym of the targeting user involved in the event.  In many events an acting user and/or actor system performs an action on a targeted user. A targeted user may be the target of actions such as create, alter, delete, log on, log off, etc.
53EE56531AA9066CE10000000A4CF109.name: UserPseudonymTargeting

5417E3D4F2E52F66E10000000A4CF109.description: The type of the target system, for example, ABAP.
5417E3D4F2E52F66E10000000A4CF109.name: SystemTypeTarget

5417E3D7F2E52F66E10000000A4CF109.description: The ID of the target system of the event, for example, SID/client ID for an ABAP system.
5417E3D7F2E52F66E10000000A4CF109.name: SystemIdTarget

547D2E96B7907331E10000000A4CF109.description: Free text that describes the health check event.
547D2E96B7907331E10000000A4CF109.name: text

547DF3D7DD747331E10000000A4CF109.description: ID of the health check event.
547DF3D7DD747331E10000000A4CF109.name: eventId

547E59BAFC1C7331E10000000A4CF109.description: Date and Time in UTC when the health check entry was created.
547E59BAFC1C7331E10000000A4CF109.name: timeStamp

549054B4240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.description: Days of validity of partitions left (partition check).
549054B4240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.name: numberDays

549054B7240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.description: Time and date when the last log entry was transferred
549054B7240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.name: lastLogTimestamp

549054B8240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.description: Time and date when the last ping was transferred
549054B8240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.name: lastPingTimestamp

549054B9240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.description: Number of User IDs in ETD
549054B9240E65D8E10000000A4CF109.name: numberUserIds

5491CA328FD665D8E10000000A4CF109.description: The text of the event instance, often called the event message.
5491CA328FD665D8E10000000A4CF109.name: EventMessage

54E69FDDFA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The local part of the hostname of the actor of the event.
54E69FDDFA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkHostnameActor

54E69FDEFA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The local part of the hostname of the target of the event.
54E69FDEFA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkHostnameTarget

54E69FE0FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The local part of the hostname of the reporter of the event.
54E69FE0FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkHostnameReporter

54E69FE1FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The MAC address of the actor of the event.
54E69FE1FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkMACAddressActor

54E69FE2FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The MAC address of the target of the event.
54E69FE2FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkMACAddressTarget

54E69FE4FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The MAC address of the reporter of the event.
54E69FE4FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkMACAddressReporter

54E69FE5FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: Uniform Resource Identifier (URI), also referred to as a URL.
54E69FE5FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: GenericURI

54E6C489FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The IP address of the actor of the event.
54E6C489FA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkIPAddressActor

54E6C48AFA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.description: The IP address of the target of the event.
54E6C48AFA728D3DE10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkIPAddressTarget

54F913D5CCC44E8AE10000000A4CF109.description: Choose this attribute if you want to select semantic events.
54F913D5CCC44E8AE10000000A4CF109.name: EventSemantic

550BD4606ACC2D7DE10000000A4CF109.description: The HTTP user agent field or other field that gives information about the client's agent program.
550BD4606ACC2D7DE10000000A4CF109.name: ServiceUserAgent

556C1851719AAC24E10000000A4CF109.description: The category of the subnetwork that includes the actor of the event. Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
556C1851719AAC24E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkSubnetCategoryActor

556C1852719AAC24E10000000A4CF109.description: The category of the subnetwork that includes the target of the event. Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
556C1852719AAC24E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkSubnetCategoryTarget

556C7EC956D9AC24E10000000A4CF109.description: The type of the reporter system, for example, ABAP.
556C7EC956D9AC24E10000000A4CF109.name: SystemTypeReporter

556C7ECA56D9AC24E10000000A4CF109.description: The ID of the reporter system of the event, for example, SID/client ID for an ABAP system.
556C7ECA56D9AC24E10000000A4CF109.name: SystemIdReporter

556CB95D730EAC24E10000000A4CF109.description: The location of the subnetwork that includes the actor of the event, for example, the name of a city. Subnetworks are managed  by administrators.
556CB95D730EAC24E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkSubnetLocationActor

556CB95E730EAC24E10000000A4CF109.description: The location of the subnetwork that includes the target of the event, for example, the name of a city. Subnetworks are managed  by administrators.
556CB95E730EAC24E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkSubnetLocationTarget

556CDFB06EFAAC24E10000000A4CF109.description: A network address that identifies the subnetwork that includes the actor of the event.  Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
556CDFB06EFAAC24E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkSubnetAddressActor

556CDFB16EFAAC24E10000000A4CF109.description: A network address that identifies the subnetwork that includes the target of the event.  Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
556CDFB16EFAAC24E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkSubnetAddressTarget

556F31400C945311E10000000A4CF109.description: The IP address of the reporter of the event.
556F31400C945311E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkIPAddressReporter

5573355759A95311E10000000A4CF109.description: The port number of the actor of the event, for example, a UDP or TCP port number.
5573355759A95311E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkPortActor

557377385BEA5311E10000000A4CF109.description: The port number of the target of the event, for example, a UDP or TCP port number.
557377385BEA5311E10000000A4CF109.name: NetworkPortTarget

55EEEDD796440756E2E225E98E57FE30.description: Pseudonym for target user. A target user is for example relevant in a user change event or an RFC scenario.
55EEEDD796440756E2E225E98E57FE30.name: targetUserPseudonym

56424E031B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The attack name, for example, a malware name.
56424E031B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: AttackName

56424E041B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The attack type, for example, malware, spoof, or denial of service.
56424E041B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: AttackType

56424E051B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: Used to correlate log instances at a lower level of a hierarchy of related instances, for example, the connection ID of an SAP passport.
56424E051B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: CorrelationSubId

56424E061B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The scenario role of the actor, for example, client, server, or proxy. An example of a scenario is a client-server scenario where one system plays the role of the client and the other the role of the server.
56424E061B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: EventScenarioRoleOfActor

56424E081B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The ID of the source of the event, for example, a hostname of a syslog server.
56424E081B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: EventSourceId

56424E091B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of the source of the event, for example, a syslog server.
56424E091B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: EventSourceType

56424E0A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A general category for various purposes, for example, the category of a web site, such as sports or news.
56424E0A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericCategory

56424E0B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of a device, usually an end user device, for example, an android phone.
56424E0B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericDeviceType

56424E0C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: An explanation of an action or attack, etc. Use 'Generic Outcome Reason'  for the reason for an outcome. This is for more general explanatory text.
56424E0C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericExplanation

56424E0D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A code for the geographic location of the initiator of the event. This code is found in some logs at network level.
56424E0D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericGeolocationCodeInitiator

56424E0E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A code for the geographic location of the target of the event. This code is found in some logs at network level.
56424E0E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericGeolocationCodeTarget

56424E0F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The order of something. This can be used for the numbered step of a workflow, for example.
56424E0F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericOrder

56424E101B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The outcome of actions or processes. Use 'Service Outcome' for codes returned by services like HTTP servers.
56424E101B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericOutcome

56424E111B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The reason for the outcome of an action, a service call, or other happening.
56424E111B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericOutcomeReason

56424E121B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A path, for example, a path of a URL or other hierarchical structure. Use 'Resource Name' for a filename. Include the directory path, if any, in 'Resource Name', rather than in this attribute.
56424E121B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericPath

56424E131B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The prior path is used in case there are two paths in an event. If there are two, one is the prior, and the other is just the path.
56424E131B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericPathPrior

56424E141B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The purpose of the log instance. For example, an SAP Read Access Log instance might specify a purpose such as verification of conformance to a particular regulatory requirement.
56424E141B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericPurpose

56424E151B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The ID of a session, usually a user session. This is an application level session ID. Use 'Network Session ID' for a network-level connection ID.
56424E151B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: GenericSessionId

56424E171B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The local part of the hostname of the intermediary of the event.
56424E171B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkHostnameIntermediary

56424E181B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The domain part of the hostname of the actor of the event.
56424E181B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkHostDomainActor

56424E191B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The domain part of the hostname of the initiator of the event.
56424E191B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkHostDomainInitiator

56424E1A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The domain part of the hostname of the intermediary of the event.
56424E1A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkHostDomainIntermediary

56424E1B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The domain part of the hostname of the reporter of the event.
56424E1B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkHostDomainReporter

56424E1C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The domain part of the hostname of the target of the event.
56424E1C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkHostDomainTarget

56424E1D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a network interface that connects to the initiator. The network interface is part of the actor.
56424E1D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkInterfaceInitiator

56424E1E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a network interface that connects to the target. The network interface is part of the actor.
56424E1E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkInterfaceTarget

56424E1F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The IP address of the initiator of the event.
56424E1F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkIPAddressInitiator

56424E201B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The IP address of the intermediary of the event.
56424E201B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkIPAddressIntermediary

56424E211B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The IP address of the initiator of the event before network address translation (NAT). The IP Address after NAT is in 'Network IP Address'.
56424E211B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkIPBeforeNATInitiator

56424E221B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The IP address of the target of the event before network address translation (NAT). The IP Address after NAT is in 'Network IP Address'.
56424E221B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkIPBeforeNATTarget

56424E231B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The MAC address of the initiator of the event.
56424E231B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkMACAddressInitiator

56424E241B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The MAC address of the intermediary of the event.
56424E241B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkMACAddressIntermediary

56424E251B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The subnetwork for the initiator, for example, an IP prefix, reported in network level logs. It is represented as an IP address and number, where number is the length of the prefix in bits, for example, 24.
56424E251B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkNetworkPrefixInitiator

56424E261B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The subnetwork for the target, for example, an IP prefix, reported in network level logs. It is represented as an IP address and number, where number is the length of the prefix in bits, for example, 24.
56424E261B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkNetworkPrefixTarget

56424E271B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The port number of the initiator of the event, for example, a UDP or TCP port number.
56424E271B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkPortInitiator

56424E281B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The port number of the intermediary of the event, for example, a UDP or TCP port number.
56424E281B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkPortIntermediary

56424E291B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The port number of the reporter of the event, for example, a UDP or TCP port number.
56424E291B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkPortReporter

56424E2A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The initiator port number before Network Address Translation (NAT). The port number after NAT is in 'network, port'.
56424E2A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkPortBeforeNATInitiator

56424E2B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The target port number before Network Address Translation (NAT). The port number after NAT is in 'network, port'.
56424E2B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkPortBeforeNATTarget

56424E2C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The protocol of the packet, for example, ICMP, TCP, or UDP. This is a code or name from IANA, or a vendor-specific protocol name.
56424E2C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkProtocol

56424E2D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: Session or connection ID at network level. Use 'Generic session ID' for an application level session ID.
56424E2D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSessionId

56424E2E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A network address that identifies the subnetwork that includes the initiator of the event.  Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
56424E2E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetAddressInitiator

56424E2F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A network address that identifies the subnetwork that includes the intermediary of the event.  Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
56424E2F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetAddressIntermediary

56424E301B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A network address that identifies the subnetwork that includes the reporter of the event.  Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
56424E301B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetAddressReporter

56424E311B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The category of the subnetwork that includes the initiator of the event. Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
56424E311B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetCategoryInitiator

56424E321B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The category of the subnetwork that includes the intermediary of the event. Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
56424E321B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetCategoryIntermediary

56424E331B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The category of the subnetwork that includes the reporter of the event. Subnetworks are managed by administrators.
56424E331B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetCategoryReporter

56424E341B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The location of the subnetwork that includes the initiator of the event, for example, the name of a city. Subnetworks are managed  by administrators.
56424E341B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetLocationInitiator

56424E351B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The location of the subnetwork that includes the intermediary of the event, for example, the name of a city. Subnetworks are managed  by administrators.
56424E351B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetLocationIntermediary

56424E361B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The location of the subnetwork that includes the reporter of the event, for example, the name of a city. Subnetworks are managed  by administrators.
56424E361B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkSubnetLocationReporter

56424E3A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A name for an area of a network, for example, the user zone, the server zone, or the Internet zone. The named area is the area of the initiator of the event. Zones may occur in network level logs.
56424E3A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkZoneInitiator

56424E3B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A name for an area of a network, for example, the user zone, the server zone, or the Internet zone. The named area is the area of the target of the event. Zones may occur in network level logs.
56424E3B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: NetworkZoneTarget

56424E3C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The direction of a parameter that gives the context for other parameters, for example, an employee ID field in a Dynpro application could be the context for other fields containing data about this employee. The direction can be input, output, or input and output.
56424E3C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterDirectionContext

56424E3D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a parameter. For Read Access Logging, this is the technical name of a field, that is, a service argument if the access channel is an API, or a screen element name, if the access channel is a User Interface (UI).
56424E3D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterName

56424E3E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a parameter that gives the context for other parameters, for example, an employee ID field in a Dynpro application could be the context for other fields containing data about this employee.
56424E3E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterNameContext

56424E3F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The datatype of the parameter, for example, numeric, string or timestamp.
56424E3F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterDataType

56424E401B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The datatype of a context parameter, for example, string or numeric.
56424E401B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterDataTypeContext

56424E411B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of a parameter. Types of parameters include attributes, features, states, configuration settings, etc. For Read Access Logging, this is the log domain name, a name which provides some semantics for technical names.
56424E411B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterType

56424E421B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of the context parameter. For Read Access Logging, this is the log domain.
56424E421B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterTypeContext

56424E431B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a numeric parameter.
56424E431B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueNumber

56424E441B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a numeric context parameter.
56424E441B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueNumberContext

56424E451B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a numeric parameter prior to a modification.
56424E451B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueNumberPriorValue

56424E471B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a string context parameter.
56424E471B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueStringContext

56424E481B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a string parameter prior to a modification.
56424E481B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueStringPriorValue

56424E491B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a floating point numeric parameter.
56424E491B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueDouble

56424E4A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a floating point numeric parameter prior to a modification.
56424E4A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueDoublePriorValue

56424E4B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a timestamp parameter.
56424E4B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueTimestamp

56424E4C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The value of a timestamp parameter prior to a modification.
56424E4C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ParameterValueTimestampPriorValue

56424E4D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: Indicates if the granted privileges can be granted to others by the grantee, the receiver of the privileges.
56424E4D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: PrivilegeIsGrantable

56424E501B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a grantee, a receiver of privileges.
56424E501B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: PrivilegeGranteeName

56424E511B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of a grantee, a receiver of privileges. If the type is user, then 'username, targeted' and 'privilege, grantee name' should both contain the username of the grantee.
56424E511B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: PrivilegeGranteeType

56424E521B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a resource container.
56424E521B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceContainerName

56424E531B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of a resource container, for example, a database schema or a data repository.
56424E531B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceContainerType

56424E541B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: Either a hash of the content of a resource or simply the content of the resource. A hash is often used to check the integrity of the content. A mismatch between the computed hash and the given hash indicates that the content has been modified.
56424E541B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceContentOrHash

56424E551B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of content of a resource, for example, a MIME type.
56424E551B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceContentType

56424E561B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The number of countable resources. Use 'resource type' for the type of the resource counted.
56424E561B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceCount

56424E571B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a resource, for example, a filename, a database table name, etc. Not all resources are named, for example, a message has a type, but not usually a name. Use this attribute for a filename and include the directory path, if any.
56424E571B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceName

56424E581B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a prior resource, for example, if the event reports the execution of a command like 'copy /sys/x.exe to /com/y.exe', this is the name of the  'from file','/sys/x.exe'. The name of the 'to filename', '/com/y.exe' goes in 'resource name'.
56424E581B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceNamePrior

56424E591B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The size of a request message, for example, an HTTP request. The units of measure for the size, for example, 'byte', are in 'resource, units of measure'.
56424E591B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceRequestSize

56424E5A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The size of a response message, for example, an HTTP response. The units of measure for the size, for example, 'byte', are in 'resource, units of measure'.
56424E5A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceResponseSize

56424E5B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The length or size of the resource, usually in bytes. Use 'resource type' for the type.
56424E5B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceSize

56424E5C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of a resource involved in an event. Examples of resources are files, messages, database tables, configurations, etc.
56424E5C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceType

56424E5D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A phrase specifying what is summed over time, for example, 'matches of packets to denied list'. This sum is a count of how many packets matched a list of source IP addresses that are denied access to the network. In this case, 'resource type' would be 'packet'.
56424E5D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceSumCriteria

56424E5E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The sum over time of something related to a resource, 'resource, sum criteria' specifies what is summed.
56424E5E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceSumOverTime

56424E5F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The units of measurement for a size or sum of a resource.
56424E5F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ResourceUnitsOfMeasure

56424E601B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The HTTP referrer or other type of referrer.
56424E601B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceReferrer

56424E611B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The request line for HTTP or the command line for a program, etc.
56424E611B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceRequestLine

56424E621B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of the service running on an actor, for example, 'HTTP Client', 'FTP Server', etc. This is often related to the network protocol, which would be 'HTTP'.
56424E621B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceType

56424E631B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The version of the type of service, for example, 1.1 for HTTP.
56424E631B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceVersion

56424E641B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The syslog application name or other application name. An application is, in general, at a higher level of hierarchy than a program.
56424E641B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceApplicationName

56424E651B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of an executable whose type is identified by 'executable type'. Only use these two fields if there is a special kind of executable that does not match an existing attribute such as transaction name or program name.
56424E651B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceExecutableName

56424E661B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of an executable whose name is identified by 'executable name'. Only use these two fields if there is a special kind of executable that does not match an existing attribute such as 'transaction name' or 'program name'.
56424E661B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceExecutableType

56424E671B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The outcome of a service, for example, the code returned by an HTTP server.
56424E671B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceOutcome

56424E681B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: An identifier for a part of some service, for example, a particular library that is used across services.
56424E681B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServicePartId

56424E691B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The identifier of a process, also called PID.
56424E691B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceProcessId

56424E6A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of a workflow, the highest level of a 4-level hierarchy of execution: workflow, transaction, program, function. Note that a report is a type of program.
56424E6A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: ServiceWorkflowName

56424E6B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The ID of the initiator system of the event, for example, SID/client ID for an ABAP system.
56424E6B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: SystemIdInitiator

56424E6C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The ID of the intermediary system of the event, for example, SID/client ID for an ABAP system.
56424E6C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: SystemIdIntermediary

56424E6D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of the initiator system, for example, ABAP.
56424E6D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: SystemTypeInitiator

56424E6E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of the intermediary system, for example, ABAP.
56424E6E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: SystemTypeIntermediary

56424E6F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: An extent of time, often of an action, or of time to perform all actions leading up to the event report. For example, time to process the HTTP request, including the processing of the response.
56424E6F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: TimeDuration

56424E701B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The time at which something ends, for example, an action.
56424E701B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: TimestampOfEnd

56424E711B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The time at which something starts, for example, an action.
56424E711B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: TimestampOfStart

56424E721B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of the thing that triggered the event, and/or caused it to be logged, for example, things like timers, audit policies, security configurations, or attack signatures.
56424E721B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: TriggerNameActing

56424E731B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The name of the trigger that is the target of some action, for example, creation, modification, enablement, disablement, deletion, etc.
56424E731B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: TriggerNameTargeted

56424E741B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of thing that triggered the event, and/or caused it to be logged, for example, things like timers, audit policies, security configurations, or attack signatures.
56424E741B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: TriggerTypeActing

56424E751B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The type of a trigger that is the target of some action, for example, creation, modification, enablement, disablement, deletion, etc.
56424E751B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: TriggerTypeTargeted

56424E761B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The method of the logon, that is how the user is authenticated.
56424E761B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UserLogonMethod

56424E771B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. The domain name is the same as the system ID for an ABAP system, because the domain of validity of an ABAP user account  is an ABAP system.  An ABAP system ID is the SAP ID plus the SAP client number, for example,  CRM/00. This attribute is for the acting user's username domain name.
56424E771B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainNameActing

56424E781B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. The domain name is the same as the system ID for an ABAP system, because the domain of validity of an ABAP user account  is an ABAP system.  An ABAP system ID is the SAP ID plus the SAP client number, for example,  CRM/00. This attribute is for the initiating user's username domain name.
56424E781B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainNameInitiating

56424E791B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. The domain name is the same as the system ID for an ABAP system, because the domain of validity of an ABAP user account  is an ABAP system.  An ABAP system ID is the SAP ID plus the SAP client number, for example,  CRM/00. This attribute is for the targeted user's username domain name.
56424E791B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainNameTargeted

56424E7A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. The domain name is the same as the system ID for an ABAP system, because the domain of validity of an ABAP user account  is an ABAP system.  An ABAP system ID is the SAP ID plus the SAP client number, for example,  CRM/00. This attribute is for the targeting user's username domain name.
56424E7A1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainNameTargeting

56424E7B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. It is the same as a system type for an ABAP system, that is, ABAP is the system type. This attribute is for the acting user's username domain type.
56424E7B1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainTypeActing

56424E7C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. It is the same as a system type for an ABAP system, that is, ABAP is the system type. This attribute is for the initiating user's username domain type.
56424E7C1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainTypeInitiating

56424E7D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. It is the same as a system type for an ABAP system, that is, ABAP is the system type. This attribute is for the targeted user's username domain type.
56424E7D1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainTypeTargeted

56424E7E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: A user account is identified by a triple: 'User Account Name', 'Username Domain Type', and 'Username Domain Name'. The domain is the domain of validity of the user account name. It identifies the system that can resolve the user account name to a real user. It is the same as a system type for an ABAP system, that is, ABAP is the system type. This attribute is for the targeting user's username domain type.
56424E7E1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UsernameDomainTypeTargeting

56424E7F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The pseudonym of the initiating user involved in the event.  In many events an acting user and/or actor system performs an action on a targeted user. A targeted user may be the target of actions such as create, alter, delete, log on, log off, etc.
56424E7F1B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UserPseudonymInitiating

56424E801B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.description: The pseudonym of the targeted user involved in the event.  In many events an acting user and/or actor system performs an action on a targeted user. A targeted user may be the target of actions such as create, alter, delete, log on, log off, etc.
56424E801B2FA51BE22A044B51CC7B4D.name: UserPseudonymTargeted

56496EC9A47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.description: Role of the initiator system, for example, test, production, customizing.
56496EC9A47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.name: SystemRoleInitiator

56496ECAA47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.description: Role of the intermediary system, for example, test, production, customizing.
56496ECAA47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.name: SystemRoleIntermediary

56496ECBA47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.description: Role of the reporter system, for example, test, production, customizing.
56496ECBA47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.name: SystemRoleReporter

56496ECCA47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.description: Role of the target system, for example, test, production, customizing.
56496ECCA47ACF89E2742B5BF023A911.name: SystemRoleTarget

5656ACCEFD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.description: The scenario role of the initiator, for example, client, server, or proxy. An example of a scenario is a client-server scenario where one system plays the role of the client and the other the role of the server.
5656ACCEFD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.name: EventScenarioRoleOfInitiator

5656ACD9FD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.description: For an ABAP system, this is the user group in user master maintenance. The targeted user belongs to this group.
5656ACD9FD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.name: UserGroupTargeted

5656ACDFFD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.description: The department of the acting user in a company as part of the company address. It is the department name used at the customer for a customer contact person. It is usually the same as the department name used on business cards.
5656ACDFFD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.name: UserDepartmentActing

5656ACEFFD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.description: Function of the acting user, for example, as contact person in a company. This is often part of the formatted address.
5656ACEFFD145AE8E2C6090F54781CD7.name: UserFunctionActing

565AC85828C52962E10000000A600446.description: Difference in criticality level compared to the previous check execution.
565AC85828C52962E10000000A600446.name: StatusDelta

566ED746F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The role of the system group that the actor system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and type. Examples of roles are: test, production, and customizing.
566ED746F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupRoleActor

566ED747F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The role of the system group that the initiator system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and type. Examples of roles are: test, production, and customizing.
566ED747F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupRoleInitiator

566ED748F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The role of the system group that the intermediary system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and type. Examples of roles are: test, production, and customizing.
566ED748F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupRoleIntermediary

566ED749F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The role of the system group that the reporter system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and type. Examples of roles are: test, production, and customizing.
566ED749F4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupRoleReporter

566ED74AF4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The role of the system group that the target system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and type. Examples of roles are: test, production, and customizing.
566ED74AF4E97FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupRoleTarget

566EE95DE8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The ID of the system group that the actor system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE95DE8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupIdActor

566EE95EE8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The ID of the system group that the initiator system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE95EE8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupIdInitiator

566EE95FE8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The ID of the system group that the intermediary system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE95FE8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupIdIntermediary

566EE960E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The ID of the system group that the reporter system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE960E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupIdReporter

566EE961E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The ID of the system group that the target system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE961E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupIdTarget

566EE962E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The type of the system group that the actor system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE962E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupTypeActor

566EE963E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The type of the system group that the initiator system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE963E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupTypeInitiator

566EE964E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The type of the system group that the intermediary system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE964E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupTypeIntermediary

566EE965E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The type of the system group that the reporter system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE965E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupTypeReporter

566EE966E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.description: The type of the system group that the target system belongs to. All systems that belong to the same system group have the same system group ID and  type.
566EE966E8F37FADE2FBD9C054838D99.name: SystemGroupTypeTarget

5672D285E9037FADE2D0D9C054838D99.description: A software building block within an application that enables a set of department-oriented business processes or cross-functional business processes. Application components can offer services to support these business processes. Application components are not implemented in a stand-alone manner. The application component and the software component come from the object directory as part of ETD master data extraction.
5672D285E9037FADE2D0D9C054838D99.name: ServiceApplicationComponent

5672D286E9037FADE2D0D9C054838D99.description: A set of SAP software objects that are grouped in development classes and can only be delivered together. For example, SAP CRM. The application component and the software component come from the object directory as part of ETD master data extraction.
5672D286E9037FADE2D0D9C054838D99.name: ServiceSoftwareComponent

5695B219365D2C9EE200460C83479BA6.description: A number representing the importance of an event or other thing that can be assigned an importance. The larger the score, the more important the thing. Usually the score ranges from zero to one hundred.
5695B219365D2C9EE200460C83479BA6.name: GenericScore

5696D00761D02C9AE2AB1A9FC7D31CA9.description: The location of the actor system as defined in the Locations application.
5696D00761D02C9AE2AB1A9FC7D31CA9.name: SystemLocationActor

5696D00861D02C9AE2AB1A9FC7D31CA9.description: The location of the initiator system as defined in the Locations application.
5696D00861D02C9AE2AB1A9FC7D31CA9.name: SystemLocationInitiator

5696D00961D02C9AE2AB1A9FC7D31CA9.description: The location of the intermediary system as defined in the Locations application.
